вҠў question
  yield topic вүЎ "How do production systems verify LLM outputs? Survey approaches, tools, and tradeoffs."

вҠў scan-academic
  given questionвҶ’topic
  yield papers
  вҲҙ Survey academic research on В«topicВ». List 6-8 key papers or approaches with one-sentence summaries. Format as a JSON array of objects: [{"name": "...", "approach": "...", "key_insight": "..."}].
  вҠЁ papers is a valid JSON array

вҠў scan-industry
  given questionвҶ’topic
  yield tools
  вҲҙ Survey production tools and frameworks for LLM output verification. Cover Guardrails AI, NeMo Guardrails, LMQL, Guidance, Outlines, Instructor, and others you know. Format as a JSON array: [{"name": "...", "type": "...", "mechanism": "..."}].
  вҠЁ tools is a valid JSON array

вҠў scan-patterns
  given questionвҶ’topic
  yield patterns
  вҲҙ Identify recurring design patterns for verifying LLM output. Categories: structural (schema validation), semantic (meaning checks), statistical (distribution monitoring), adversarial (red-teaming), human-in-loop. For each give name, description, when to use it. JSON array format.
  вҠЁ patterns is a valid JSON array

вҠў cross-reference
  given scan-academicвҶ’papers
  given scan-industryвҶ’tools
  given scan-patternsвҶ’patterns
  yield matrix
  вҲҙ Cross-reference the research. For each tool in В«toolsВ», identify which patterns from В«patternsВ» it implements and which papers from В«papersВ» it draws from. Produce a markdown table with columns: Tool | Patterns Used | Related Papers | Gaps.
  вҠЁ matrix is not empty

вҠў assess-for-cell
  given scan-patternsвҶ’patterns
  given cross-referenceвҶ’matrix
  yield recommendations
  вҲҙ Cell uses two oracle types: deterministic (SQL checks like length_matches, is_json_array, not_empty) and semantic (LLM-judged assertions). Given the patterns in В«patternsВ» and the landscape in В«matrixВ», what verification approaches should Cell adopt next? Rank by impact Г— implementation ease. Numbered list, 5 items max.
  вҠЁ recommendations is not empty

вҠў build-index
  given scan-academicвҶ’papers
  given scan-industryвҶ’tools
  given scan-patternsвҶ’patterns
  given cross-referenceвҶ’matrix
  given assess-for-cellвҶ’recommendations
  yield index
  вҲҙ Compile a structured research index from all upstream findings. Sections: (1) Executive Summary (3 sentences), (2) Academic Landscape [В«papersВ»], (3) Production Tools [В«toolsВ»], (4) Design Patterns [В«patternsВ»], (5) Cross-Reference Matrix [В«matrixВ»], (6) Recommendations for Cell [В«recommendationsВ»]. Markdown format.
  вҠЁ index is not empty
